e.py:148:    # Prepare dataset\ncode/LLM-DetectAIve/pipeline/model_pipeline.py:149:    dataset = prepare_dataset(file_path, labels_dict, sample_frac=sample_frac)\ncode/LLM-DetectAIve/pipeline/model_pipeline.py:156:    # Tokenize dataset\ncode/LLM-DetectAIve/pipeline/model_pipeline.py:157:    tokenized_datasets = tokenize_and_prepare_dataset(dataset, tokenizer)\ncode/LLM-DetectAIve/pipeline/model_pipeline.py:159:    # Save tokenized dataset\ncode/LLM-DetectAIve/pipeline/model_pipeline.py:160:    save_tokenized_dataset(tokenized_datasets, f\"{save_dir}/tokenized_{model_name}\")\ncode/LLM-DetectAIve/pipeline/model_pipeline.py:163:    trainer, trained_model = train_model(model_name, tokenized_datasets, num_labels, num_trials, num_epochs)\ncode/LLM-DetectAIve/pipeline/model_pipeline.py:166:    evaluate_model(trainer, tokenized_datasets)\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/subtaskC/baseline/requirements.txt:7:huggingface-hub==0.17.2\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/subtaskC/baseline/requirements.txt:47:tzdata==2023.3\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:10:[News](#news) | [Competition](#competition) | [Subtasks](#subtasks) | [Data Source](#data_source) | [Data Format](#data_format) | [Evaluation Metrics](#scorer_and_official_evaluation_metrics) | [Baselines](#baselines) | [FAQ](#faq) | [Organizers](#organizers) | [Contacts](#contacts)\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:57:Note that additional training data is **NOT allowed** for all participants.\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:59:## <a name=\"data_source\"></a>Data Source\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:60:The data for the task is an extension of the M4 dataset. Here are current statistics about the dataset.\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:63:    <a><img src=\"images/data_statistics.png\" alt=\"Title\" style=\"width: 80%; min-width: 250px; display: block; margin: auto;\"></a>\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:67:The M4 dataset is described in an [EACL'2024 paper -- Best Resource Paper Award](https://aclanthology.org/2024.eacl-long.83/):\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:70:    title = \"M4: Multi-generator, Multi-domain, and Multi-lingual Black-Box Machine-Generated Text Detection\",\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:95:    abstract = \"Large language models (LLMs) have demonstrated remarkable capability to generate fluent responses to a wide variety of user queries. However, this has also raised concerns about the potential misuse of such texts in journalism, education, and academia. In this study, we strive to create automated systems that can detect machine-generated texts and pinpoint potential misuse. We first introduce a large-scale benchmark M4, which is a multi-generator, multi-domain, and multi-lingual corpus for machine-generated text detection. Through an extensive empirical study of this dataset, we show that it is challenging for detectors to generalize well on instances from unseen domains or LLMs. In such cases, detectors tend to misclassify machine-generated text as human-written. These results show that the problem is far from solved and that there is a lot of room for improvement. We believe that our dataset will enable future research towards more robust approaches to this pressing societal problem. The dataset is available at https://github.com/mbzuai-nlp/M4\",\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:115:## <a name=\"data_format\"></a>Data Format\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:118:To download the dataset for this project, follow these steps:\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:126:2. Use `gdown` to download the dataset folders by providing the respective file IDs for each subtask:\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:130:| Whole dataset | [Google Drive Folder](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/14DulzxuH5TDhXtviRVXsH5e2JTY2POLi)            | 14DulzxuH5TDhXtviRVXsH5e2JTY2POLi            |\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:138:Make sure to replace `<file_id>` with the respective file IDs provided above when running the `gdown` command for the desired dataset.\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:140:3. After downloading place the files in their respective subtask folder.\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:143:The datasets are JSONL files.\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:144:The data is located in the following folders:\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:147:    * subtaskA/data/subtaskA_train_monolingual.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:148:    * subtaskA/data/subtaskA_dev_monolingual.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:150:    * subtaskA/data/subtaskA_train_multilingual.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:151:    * subtaskA/data/subtaskA_dev_multilingual.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:153:  * subtaskB/data/subtaskB_train.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:154:  * subtaskB/data/subtaskB_dev.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:156:  * subtaskC/data/subtaskC_train.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:157:  * subtaskC/data/subtaskC_dev.jsonl\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:178:  model -> model that generated the data,\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:190:  model -> model name that generated data,\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:307:#### Q: Could you please tell me what the differences are between our task’s dataset and the M4 dataset? Are they absolutely the same?\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:309:**A:** There are mainly three major differences compared to the M4 dataset: 1) task formulation is different, 2) we upsampled human text for data balance; and 3) new and surprising domains, generators and languages will appear in test sets (real test set will not include information about generators, domains and languages).\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:315:#### Q: Whether it is allowed to use additional data?\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/README.md:317:**A:** It is not allowed to use extra data.\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/subtaskC/baseline/run.sh:6:  --train_file \"../data/subtaskC_train.jsonl\" \\\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/subtaskC/baseline/run.sh:8:  --dev_file \"../data/subtaskC_dev.jsonl\" \\\ncode/SemEval2024-task8/su