{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_94","type":"agent_message","text":"The resource-gathering pass is complete. I set up an isolated `uv` environment in this workspace, downloaded 8 papers into [papers](/workspaces/llm-reading-modes-af09-codex/papers), staged datasets under [datasets](/workspaces/llm-reading-modes-af09-codex/datasets), cloned 3 relevant repos into [code](/workspaces/llm-reading-modes-af09-codex/code), and wrote the synthesis in [literature_review.md](/workspaces/llm-reading-modes-af09-codex/literature_review.md) and [resources.md](/workspaces/llm-reading-modes-af09-codex/resources.md). The completion marker is [`.resource_finder_complete`](/workspaces/llm-reading-modes-af09-codex/.resource_finder_complete).\n\nThe strongest gathered assets for the actual hypothesis are SemEval Task 8 Subtask B for source-mode attribution, SemEval Task 8 Subtask C for mixed-authorship boundary detection, and LLM-DetectAIve plus TextMachina for extending beyond binary labels into process-style modes like machine-humanized or machine-polished text. For the “dictated/spoken” angle, I found and documented the SWAB/CoS2W literature and staged a small LibriSpeech transcript proxy, but there is still a gap in a clean public dictated-vs-written benchmark. For keyboard-layout and typo-pattern modes, the review concludes that synthetic data generation will likely be necessary.\n\nValidation was limited to resource checks, schema inspection, sample extraction, and repository/documentation inspection. The local `paper-finder` helper did not return promptly, so the paper search was completed manually."}}
